config SIDEWALK_MESSAGE_SIZE
	int "Maximum length of message"
	default 256
	help
	  Sets maximum length of receved message from aws.
	  Keep in mind that you're dealing with limited memory so setting the number too high can cause to take too much space.

config SIDEWALK_MESSAGE_QUEUE_SIZE
	int "Maximum size of queue"
	default 20
	help
	  Sets maximum size of queue that recieves messages.
	  This will prevent from recieving too many messages and overloading RAM of board.
	  Keep in mind that you're dealing with limited memory so setting the number too high can cause to take too much space.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"